I too tend to prefer ASCII art because it can be viewed reliably on a web page and in a text editor. Ideally you could make it in HTML/Wiki but still have it copiable as text, with the web browser doing a decent job of conversion to text. The downside of ASCII of course is the lack of meta-information; content and structure are intertwined. What do your attempts look like so far?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Mar 30, 2010 5:14 pm</p><hr />
